name: Women's Big Book Study and Writing Meeting - 8:30 pm Eastern - Online
notes:
Zoom ID: 858-0503-9409
Passcode: EDA4Women

We gather for approximately 90 minutes

THE THREE Rs
Reading, (W)riting, and Recovery

• Following the standard opening of the meeting, we will read a portion of the EDA Big Book, and write for approximately 15 minutes, focusing on what was just read or anything related to our EDA recovery.
• The last portion of the meeting will be open for members to read and / or share about what they wrote.
• Please have your EDA Big Book and your writing notebook readily accessible.
• This is meant to be a nonjudgmental, safe environment. It is not a critique group. We encourage acceptance, acknowledgment, and appreciation of any and all writing.
• All present are encouraged to share, therefore the meeting may run over an hour, but no more than 90 minutes, depending on the number of people in attendance.
